SIMPLE: protraction
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Protraction
<hw>Pro*trac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>protractio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A drawing out, or
continuing; the act of delaying the termination of a thing;
prolongation; continuance; delay; <as>as, the <ex>protraction</ex> of a
debate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>protraction</qex> only of what is worst in life.</q>
<rj><qau>Mallock.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surv.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The act or process
of making a plot on paper.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A plot on
paper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protractive</ent>⟦br⟧
